[thinking] **Addressing SLF4J Issues**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether the H2 dependency includes the SLF4J optional jar. If it doesn’t, it leads to `NoClassDef` errors when trying to invoke `Class.forName`. Maybe adding `testImplementation slf4j-simple` could help. I could create minimal `Logger` and `LoggerFactory` stubs in my tests. If H2’s POM doesn’t compile SLF4J, I can test with stubs during the test classpath. I’m curious if adding fake external libraries for this purpose is okay, since they could help demonstrate optional behaviors.
