[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering the global serializer settings and how the `JdbcUtils` static block activates upon its first access. If the `DatabaseTest.Serializer` constructor runs correctly, it should serialize to a string. With `H2Test`, if I'm serializing a non-string, `String.valueOf` should handle that fine. I wonder if I should create a dedicated top-level serializer instead of an inner one. Also, the `h2.javaObjectSerializer` settings intrigue me, especially how class loading impacts the system properties. It feels like there's quite a bit to juggle regarding metadata and reflection in the tests!
