imply call it, but that might open a browser in the user's environment. That said, we need to be careful about opening a new external browser. \\n\\nIn a CI environment, if there’s no browser available, it could lead to exceptions. I can make it more robust by catching exceptions and asserting true, but I need to ensure the call can open properly under different conditions.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating a test for ServerTest**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a test for the \\\"call:\\\" covering a Utils call, even if it doesn’t report anything. For ServerTest, I shouldn’t be using assertThatThrownBy, and instead, I could call it within a try-catch block. However, since openBrowser might fail when desktop is false, I’m wondering if catching an empty exception is allowed. I guess I could assert the exception message instead.\\n\\nSo, I might do something like:  \\ntry { Server.openBrowser(...); } catch (Exception expected) { assertThat(expected).isNotNull(); }  \\n\\nI just need to remember to import assertThat without causing any side effects.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NcdqdVrsgAZUFi51Dc6Ib8YN|fc_02928e0d39233fc60169f892e878c88192b8e85b4134ba66bb", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/h2/ServerTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 45757, "output": 557, "cacheRead": 8704, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55018, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777898202610, "responseId": "resp_02928e0d39233fc60169f892dc16b08192bbaee42869edb8f9"}}
